libvirt
- is a toolkit to manage virtualization platforms
- is accessible from C, Python, Perl, Java and more
- is licensed under open source licenses
- supports KVM, QEMU, Xen, Virtuozzo, VMWare ESX, LXC, BHyve and more
- targets Linux and other OSes
- is used by many applications

This template enables libvirt itself along with other components and utilities
of file systems and networking, and kernel configuration options that usually
work together.

#@TYPE: Wrtemplate
#@NAME: libvirt
#@DESCRIPTION: Enable libvirt and related components utilities and kernel options
